# .aidocs/project-update.aidocs - /project-update Contract

Purpose
- Sync project-local AI system files to latest canonical versions without re-running full initialization.

When to use
- Use `/project-update` for projects that already ran `/project-init` and only need system/runtime refresh.

Source resolution (!!!):
- AIDOCS source path MUST be read from the global routing file (`~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` or `~/.config/opencode/AGENTS.md`), which contains `AIDOCS source: <path>`.
- Never compute, search, or guess the source path. The installer `.cmd` is the sole authority that sets this path.

Contract
- Validate project is already initialized (`/.MEMORY/` + router present).
- Copy/sync project-local system artifacts from AIDOCS source:
  - `.aidocs/index.aidocs`
  - linked shared docs
  - OpenCode/Claude project command files (`project-init`, `archive`, `project-update`, `personality`, `memory-update`, `clean`, `uber-clean`, `refactor`, `uber-refactor`)
  - `.aidocs/personalities/` directory (all personality definition files)
- Refresh project `AGENTS.md` and `CLAUDE.md` with project-local relative routes.
- Copy only missing memory template files; never overwrite existing `/.MEMORY/*`.
- Regenerate Claude Code auto-memory file:
  - Compute path: take project root absolute path, replace `:` with empty and all `\` or `/` with `-`. Target: `~/.claude/projects/<encoded>/memory/MEMORY.md`. Create directory if missing.
  - This file is auto-loaded into every Claude Code session's system prompt.
  - Must contain: memory system bootstrap instructions (how to use `/.MEMORY/`), canonical structure reference, and condensed critical learnings (`!!!`+) from `/.MEMORY/domains/*.md` and `/.MEMORY/rules/*.md`.
  - Keep under 200 lines. Full details stay in `/.MEMORY/` files.
  - MEMORY.md is READ-ONLY during normal sessions — only `/project-update` writes to it.
- Do not run ingestion/restructuring/topic-map rebuild unless explicitly requested.
- Hard gate after sync: re-read updated project routing/instructions before continuing any other task:
  1) `AGENTS.md` and/or `CLAUDE.md`
  2) `.aidocs/index.aidocs`
  3) linked shared docs from the index
  This applies in the same session (no restart required).

Safety
- Re-read `/.MEMORY/NOW.md` before planning and after compaction/session resume.
- Log update outcome to today's daily file.
